      ],
      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09D\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09D named J09D_temp\\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG\\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\\n    1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n    2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n4. JOIN this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\\n5. JOIN this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\\n    If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data.\\n    Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data.\\n7. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09D including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n8. Send them to the EVU team to meter.readings@evu.com\\n9. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data.\"}",
            "id": "lc_b14073a3-c525-4052-99dd-3b325f9b3dd3"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "505657da-a0bd-4fe9-9c6d-562e40c5b80f",
        "tool_call_id": "call_p4b7dvet",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09D",
            "process_rule": "1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09D named J09D_temp\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\n    1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\"\n    2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\"\n4. JOIN this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\n5. JOIN this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\n    If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data.\n    Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data.\n7. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09D including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n8. Send them to the EVU team to meter.readings@evu.com\n9. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
